rt\nteams, and other useful data for future research and social engineering attack',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:23:41'),(278,'#beef #tool #kali #intro #pentest','\nBeEF is a browser-based exploit package that \"hooks\" one or more\n	browsers as beachheads for launching attacks. A user can be hooked by accessing a\n	customized URL and continue to see typical web traffic, while an attacker has access\n	to the user\'s session.\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:51:37'),(279,'#beef #tool #kali #intro #pentest','ifk: beef is useful while pentester has access to the user_s session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:52:06'),(280,'#beef #tool #kali #intro #pentest','BeEF bypasses network security appliances and host–based, anti-virus applications by targeting the vulnerabilities found in common browsers, such as ff and ie',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:53:56'),(281,'#kali #tool #beef #run#server #tuto','\ncd /usr/share/beef-xss\n./beef\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 13:28:54'),(282,'#kali #tool #beef #methodology','\nu need to redirect the victim into ur beef_url_hook(in_running_server: http://127.0.0.1:3000/hook.js) \n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 13:07:08'),(283,'#kali #tool #panel #admin#beef #run #tuto','\nafter running the server of beef, \nu need to go in interface_ui|web_admin of beef:\n	go at: http://127.0.0.1:3000/ui/panel\n		which u see in the terminal of running of beef_server\n	\n	in the first time of connection to server_beef:\n		username: beef\n		password: beef\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 13:21:51'),(284,'#burp #kali #methodology #tool','\nBurp Proxy is a tool that intercepts HTTP and HTTPS traffic. It allows a Penetration\nTester to examine an application, its vulnerabilities, and the two-way traffic between\na client and a web server. Burp Proxy is very popular because of its ability to not\nonly examine the traffic, but also, it manipulates requests\n\nWhen a user enters a URL in their web 